<br>
No-one ever got burned if they stayed away from the fire. The warmth is really great, but the burning hurts. this advice is too late for now, but save it for the future. It is so easy to get caught up and it's so natural to crave what you don't have.<br>
<br>
So seldom does the lure pay off with the pleasure that it's not worth considering.<br>
<br>
You know what you have already is better than the promise. Remind yourself daily. Tell that to your 'friend'. If he is a friend, he will respect your desires beyond his own.<br>
<br>
How honest can you be with your husband? My wife and I can talk about our weaknesses and help each other out.<br>
<br>
Close your eyes. Picture your husband as you first dated him. Now open your eyes and treat him like you first treated him. Betcha He'll respond in kind.<br>
<br>
Good luck.<br>
<br>
-PoStryven<br>
